column2: The outcome of the assessment whether the applicant is homeless or threatened with homelessness and what, if any, duty is owed to them by the local authority.

Totals include Breckland, Brighton and Hove, Darlington, Halton, Haringey, Harrogate, Hounslow,  Lewes, Rother, Somerset West and Taunton, Stevenage, and Stroud who did not provide accurate data this quarter but have provided figures in previous quarters. These values were used to derive estimates.
Notice to end an Assured Shorthold Tenancy (AST) which expires within 56 days.

Only includes households assessed as homeless on initial assessment. This excludes the number of relief duties owed to households who were homeless at the end of a prevention duty - found in table P1.
Totals may not equal the sum of components because of rounding.
